<div id="review_3834638110" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3834638110" />
    <a title="Tamyka " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57788205-tamyka"><img alt="Tamyka " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1548570545p2/57788205.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3834638110?book_show_action=true">Feb 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tamyka " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tamyka " href="/user/show/57788205-tamyka">Tamyka </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3834638110" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13453929893717588502">Had this book for some years but never got around to reading it. I regret that! This book was amazing! The writing is just *chef’s kiss!! I know it’s a narrative/literary fiction but I read it like it was historical fiction. This is a great mentor text to use when teaching character development, author’s use of diction and tone and point of view. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


